  "text": "For both groups, there was a ceiling effect on the total KPCS score, especially at six months. Although skewness and kurtosis were moderate for the at-risk group (skewness − 0.67, kurtosis 0.10 at two months and − 1.28 and 2.09, respectively, at six months), they were more problematic for the not-at-risk group (skewness − 1.73, kurtosis 5.29 at two months and − 1.51 and 3.65 respectively at six months). Many items had mean values well above 2.80 and standard deviations around 0.3, for both the not-at-risk and at-risk samples. The mean of this sample is consistent with the mean of the control group (approximately 42) as reported in the original study [CITATION_1] , indicating that a ceiling effect was also present in that study.",
